# Testing and Validation

- Add unit tests for all new business logic unless explicitly waived by the user.
- Add regression tests for bug fixes when feasible.
- Cover: happy path, edge cases, invalid/boundary input, and failure/error paths.
- Prefer deterministic tests; investigate and fix flaky behavior rather than
 masking it with retries or skip flags.
- Mock external services and I/O in automated tests unless integration coverage
 is the explicit goal.
- Never remove or weaken existing tests just to make CI pass.
- Validate: concurrency, retries, race conditions, state corruption, invalid
 transitions, and rollback behavior where applicable.
